{
  "id": "10114",
  "key": "GG-111",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Ensure API Token Management and Security Best Practices",
    "description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use case:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As a "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Product Owner",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "I want to ensure API token management and security best practices, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "so that sensitive credentials are handled securely and never exposed in logs or version control."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Acceptance criteria:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "GIVEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the need to connect to Jira Cloud using the official REST API, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "WHEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " collecting Jira Cloud credentials (API tokens or OAuth) and the project key or ID, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AND",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " storing them on the backend, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "THEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " sensitive data is encrypted and securely stored following industry best practices."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Technical notes:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The Node JS backend should utilize secure methods for storing sensitive data such as API tokens. It should avoid hardcoding credentials and instead use secure environmental variables or a secure credential storage mechanism. The backend must implement encryption and proper access control to ensure that API tokens are protected from unauthorized access. Furthermore, any logging mechanisms should be designed to exclude sensitive information such as tokens. The team must refer to OWASP best practices for secure credential storage and handlement."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
